100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 7, 1925, the world was abuzz with the news of the first public demonstration of the new television technology in London, showcasing a potential revolution in entertainment and communication. Meanwhile, political tensions escalated in Germany, with the government grappling with economic challenges and the rise of extremist movements. In the United States, discussions continued around Prohibition, as debates raged over its efficacy and impact on society.
